Title: The Halo Mass Function of Late-Type Galaxies from HI Kinematics
Authors: P. Li, F. Lelli, S.S. McGaugh, M.S. Pawlowski, M. Zwaan, J.M. Schombert
================================================================================
Byte-by-byte Description of file: WP50_M200.mrt
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
   Bytes Format Units         Label       Explanations
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
   1- 12 A12    -             Name        Galaxy Name
  13- 19 F6.2   km/s          WP50        HI linewidth at 50% of the peak flux
  20- 25 F5.2   km/s        e_WP50        Mean error on WP50
  26- 31 F5.2   solMass       log(M_NFW)  Halo mass for NFW model (1)
  32- 36 F4.2   solMass     e_log(M_NFW)  Mean error on log(M_NFW)
  37- 42 F5.2   solMass       log(M_Ein)  Halo mass for Einasto model (1)
  43- 47 F4.2   solMass     e_log(M_Ein)  Mean error on log(M_Ein)
  48- 53 F5.2   solMass       log(M_DC14) Halo mass for DC14 model (1)
  54- 58 F4.2   solMass     e_log(M_DC14) Mean error on log(M_DC14)
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
(1) The halo mass is defined at R200, the radius where the dark matter density
    is 200 times the critical density of the Universe.
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
